											<section class="main bio authorbio">
							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/bas-den-hond/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Bas den Hond is a Dutch independent journalist who divides his time between rural New Hampshire in the United States, semi-rural Linschoten in the Netherlands, and urban Berlin in Germany. He has a master of science in astronomy from Utrecht University in the Netherlands. Den Hond is a US correspondent for the Dutch newspaper <em>Trouw</em>. His science writing has also appeared in <em>Eos</em>, <em>New Scientist</em>, <em>Science News</em>, <em>The Economist</em>, and the Dutch weekly news magazine <em>EW</em>.</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="520" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/basbio-520x520.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/basbio-520x520.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/basbio-150x150.jpg 150w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/basbio-768x768.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/basbio-900x900.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/basbio.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
